Krill's Loader, repository version 194 (Plush)
Source: https://csdb.dk/release/?id=226124
Download: https://csdb.dk/getinternalfile.php/238373/loader-v194.zip
License: see loader/README (free to use; BSD-style disclaimer)

Built locally with ca65 (brew cc65) via:
  EXTCONFIGPATH=../ourconfig make PLATFORM=c64 prg INSTALL=0900 RESIDENT=0200 ZP=e0
Config trimmed in ourconfig/loaderconfig.inc:
  ONLY_1541_AND_COMPATIBLE=1, DECOMPRESSOR=ZX0, LOAD_COMPD_API=1
Produces: loader/build/install-c64.prg ($0900-$1597),
          loader/build/loader-c64.prg ($0200-$0406), loadersymbols-c64.inc
  The ZX0 decompressor is what pushes the resident past $02DF to $0406 --
  three pages, not two. Anything that scribbles on low memory (error codes,
  diagnostics) must stay clear of $0200-$0406; see ERR_CODE in src/boot.asm.
IMPORTANT usage constraints found the hard way (see notes/slideshow.md):
  - $DD00 writes while the loader is resident: upper 6 bits MUST be 0
  - resident at $0200 overlaps KERNAL kbd buffer/RS232 vars: SEI before
    copying it there and never return to BASIC/KERNAL afterwards
